    "body": "<small>Note: Used AI to assist. Reviewed code and tested manually.</small>\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n#40009 — surfaced in 0.12.2. On Windows the embedded server first used a hidden\r\n`AllocConsole` (for `:terminal` + detach/restart), which broke SIXEL/Kitty `io.stdout` rendering (#38667) and Ctrl-C in `:terminal` (#38630). #38669 fixed both by switching to `AttachConsole(ATTACH_PARENT_PROCESS)`, borrowing the parent\r\nterminal's console so `CONOUT$` points at the real terminal again (though rendering on `:restart` won't work because of `AllocConsole()`). But now the server's stdio handles refer to that console (CON), and channel jobs inherit\r\nthem — so libuv spawns them without `CREATE_NO_WINDOW`, leaving the child on the shared console. \r\nA job writing directly to CON (e.g. gutentags) then draws over the TUI until a redraw. \r\nIt only showed up now because the earlier hidden console swallowed such writes.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nAdded a Windows-only `stdio_noinherit` flag for channel jobs. When set, child `stdin` and `stderr` use `UV_CREATE_PIPE` instead of inherited handles, allowing libuv to use `CREATE_NO_WINDOW` and preventing `CON` writes from leaking onto the TUI.",
    "closed_at": null,
